1
00:00:00,220 --> 00:00:01,380
(Previously)
What do I do, Pa?

2
00:00:01,980 --> 00:00:04,701
Seems like I'm losing my crush at work
to that Pom-eranian dude.

3
00:00:05,936 --> 00:00:08,910
You know cats are bad for your health.

4
00:00:09,216 --> 00:00:10,646
Why are you still obsessed with them?

5
00:00:10,670 --> 00:00:12,104
As my son…

6
00:00:12,652 --> 00:00:13,700
Are you going to stop me?

7
00:00:14,223 --> 00:00:15,424
You're not allowed to give up.

8
00:00:15,619 --> 00:00:16,899
You used to ask me…

9
00:00:17,272 --> 00:00:19,913
which one is my favorite cat, right?

10
00:00:21,328 --> 00:00:22,328
You…

11
00:00:23,389 --> 00:00:24,809
You are my favorite cat.

12
00:00:27,966 --> 00:00:29,308
Let's go on a date next week.

13
00:00:33,837 --> 00:00:36,119
They say it's storm season, Granny Juu.

14
00:00:36,575 --> 00:00:39,009
I can't help feeling sorry
for those cats without shelter.

15
00:00:39,528 --> 00:00:46,106
(I hope some kids come by
and take shelter from the rain.)

16
00:01:09,087 --> 00:01:10,087
Want an umbrella?

17
00:01:11,116 --> 00:01:13,696
It's a storm, so it might be a while
before the rain stops.

18
00:01:14,802 --> 00:01:15,802
Or…

19
00:01:16,945 --> 00:01:18,025
would you rather stay here?

20
00:01:19,291 --> 00:01:20,291
That's fine.

21
00:01:23,608 --> 00:01:25,094
Want to come inside and take shelter?

22
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:39,400
"Cat for Cash"
(Episode 5)

23
00:02:44,656 --> 00:02:45,936
Have you decided

24
00:02:46,220 --> 00:02:47,505
where you want our date to be?

25
00:02:47,774 --> 00:02:49,620
Huh? What date?

26
00:02:50,207 --> 00:02:52,084
I never said I'd go with you.

27
00:02:53,114 --> 00:02:54,114
That's fine

28
00:02:54,445 --> 00:02:55,694
if you can't decide yet.

29
00:02:56,547 --> 00:02:57,547
I can wait.

30
00:02:58,325 --> 00:03:01,813
Working at the cat café with you
already feels like a date every day anyway.

31
00:03:03,865 --> 00:03:04,924
If that's a date,

32
00:03:05,283 --> 00:03:07,393
why am I scooping the litter boxes
every single day?

33
00:03:10,598 --> 00:03:13,128
So the birthday gifts for the cats
were your idea?

34
00:03:14,439 --> 00:03:15,624
It was Madam Meow's idea.

35
00:03:16,574 --> 00:03:19,035
No wonder she never paid off
what she owed you.

36
00:03:19,675 --> 00:03:21,311
Three birthdays this month alone.

37
00:03:24,357 --> 00:03:25,636
One, two…

38
00:03:29,707 --> 00:03:30,707
three.

39
00:03:33,404 --> 00:03:34,404
Let's go.

40
00:03:43,518 --> 00:03:44,518
We've got everything.

41
00:03:45,824 --> 00:03:46,849
I don't think so.

42
00:03:47,702 --> 00:03:49,386
One more cat has a birthday
this month too.

43
00:03:50,581 --> 00:03:51,581
Which one?

44
00:03:51,764 --> 00:03:52,853
I already checked them all.

45
00:03:53,016 --> 00:03:55,680
The one who's handsome,

46
00:03:56,406 --> 00:03:58,913
kind, has time for you,

47
00:03:59,716 --> 00:04:01,213
and helps scoop the litter boxes too.

48
00:04:01,647 --> 00:04:03,516
If that cat is a good boy,

49
00:04:04,973 --> 00:04:06,207
I might think about it.

50
00:04:06,581 --> 00:04:08,981
That cat's always been well-behaved.

51
00:04:15,104 --> 00:04:16,104
You know that.

52
00:04:22,953 --> 00:04:24,019
Yeah. I hope so.

53
00:04:26,265 --> 00:04:27,265
Meow~

54
00:04:36,865 --> 00:04:37,865
Krapor.

55
00:04:38,424 --> 00:04:39,424
Why are you here?

56
00:04:39,762 --> 00:04:40,762
We're closed today.

57
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:42,966
Isn't it obvious from the way

58
00:04:43,086 --> 00:04:44,086
I'm standing?

59
00:04:44,165 --> 00:04:45,179
I've got teen probs.

60
00:04:46,024 --> 00:04:48,521
So I came to have Granny Juu
read my fortune.

61
00:04:50,483 --> 00:04:51,483
Ahhh.

62
00:04:51,607 --> 00:04:52,621
What? Our Granny Juu?

63
00:04:52,701 --> 00:04:53,701
Correct.

64
00:04:54,304 --> 00:04:56,375
Cats have six senses.

65
00:04:56,589 --> 00:04:58,989
Especially ones as old as Granny Juu.

66
00:04:59,403 --> 00:05:03,011
So Je Meow opened
the Juu-Te-Lu fortune-telling corner.

67
00:05:04,801 --> 00:05:06,012
Here's the thing, Granny Juu.

68
00:05:06,413 --> 00:05:09,099
The other day, I dropped off ice
at my friend's shop.

69
00:05:09,493 --> 00:05:11,007
His little sister was there,

70
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:12,912
so I handed her the bill.

71
00:05:13,046 --> 00:05:15,403
She looked at it and said,

72
00:05:15,584 --> 00:05:19,098
"Hey, this isn't the usual price we pay."

73
00:05:19,498 --> 00:05:21,608
"Are you charging me extra, brother?"

74
00:05:21,688 --> 00:05:23,620
She asked me that.

75
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:24,780
Does that mean

76
00:05:24,826 --> 00:05:27,848
she's feeling something extra for me?

77
00:05:32,614 --> 00:05:34,613
She's picked!

78
00:05:35,180 --> 00:05:36,471
This card?

79
00:05:36,518 --> 00:05:39,219
Yes, this card. Here we go.

80
00:05:43,188 --> 00:05:44,221
It's Seven of Cups.

81
00:05:44,376 --> 00:05:46,528
What does that mean?

82
00:05:50,512 --> 00:05:51,312
It means…

83
00:05:51,357 --> 00:05:52,357
It means…?

84
00:05:57,564 --> 00:05:58,809
Stop imagining things.

85
00:06:01,071 --> 00:06:06,503
Ah, it means my friend's sister
shouldn't imagine things between us, right?

86
00:06:06,892 --> 00:06:08,126
Because in my heart,

87
00:06:08,247 --> 00:06:10,304
there's only my baby Jenny.

88
00:06:10,504 --> 00:06:11,504
Right?

89
00:06:11,695 --> 00:06:12,621
The card did read you right.

90
00:06:12,666 --> 00:06:14,733
You're so accurate, Granny Juu.

91
00:06:15,406 --> 00:06:16,406
- Hey, Krapor.
- Yes?

92
00:06:16,508 --> 00:06:18,333
- Can I have her pick a card too?
- Sure.

93
00:06:18,668 --> 00:06:20,418
Well, I…

94
00:06:20,549 --> 00:06:21,549
You…

95
00:06:22,218 --> 00:06:24,184
- I mean my friend.
- Ah, your friend.

96
00:06:24,542 --> 00:06:25,907
He has a crush on his coworker.

97
00:06:27,101 --> 00:06:28,508
So he wants to know…

98
00:06:29,876 --> 00:06:31,203
is it one-sided?

99
00:06:33,130 --> 00:06:34,295
Leave that to me, bro.

100
00:06:34,401 --> 00:06:35,818
I'll ask Granny Juu

101
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:37,854
how that person really feels
about your friend.

102
00:06:38,752 --> 00:06:39,804
Go ahead, Granny Juu.

103
00:06:40,346 --> 00:06:41,722
There she goes!

104
00:06:46,262 --> 00:06:47,262
A bad card?

105
00:06:49,630 --> 00:06:50,816
I can't read English.

106
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:52,919
Help me.

107
00:06:55,301 --> 00:06:57,080
Strength.

108
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,080
Ah, Strength card.

109
00:07:01,176 --> 00:07:02,021
Whoa.

110
00:07:02,081 --> 00:07:04,212
It says the person
your friend has a crush on

111
00:07:04,512 --> 00:07:06,411
is really charming,

112
00:07:06,672 --> 00:07:08,520
feisty, and fearless too.

113
00:07:08,627 --> 00:07:09,799
What's interesting is

114
00:07:10,839 --> 00:07:12,819
they like being around four-legged animals.

115
00:07:15,796 --> 00:07:19,200
I'm not sure about the last part.

116
00:07:20,119 --> 00:07:21,700
I always see them…

117
00:07:22,161 --> 00:07:23,561
fighting whenever they're together.

118
00:07:24,394 --> 00:07:25,919
They might seem tough on the outside,

119
00:07:26,185 --> 00:07:29,312
but they're actually
soft and sensitive inside.

120
00:07:29,806 --> 00:07:31,520
They fall for clingy people.

121
00:07:31,841 --> 00:07:33,713
Keep at it, they'll give in eventually.

122
00:07:34,457 --> 00:07:35,562
You're making stuff up.

123
00:07:36,195 --> 00:07:39,504
Granny Juu, tell him it's not that easy...

124
00:07:39,743 --> 00:07:40,743
Boom!

125
00:07:41,187 --> 00:07:42,320
There she goes again.

126
00:07:43,384 --> 00:07:44,512
Let me see.

127
00:07:44,772 --> 00:07:45,772
Ah ha.

128
00:07:48,997 --> 00:07:49,997
Three of Swords.

129
00:07:50,049 --> 00:07:51,215
It means a love triangle.

130
00:07:51,637 --> 00:07:52,637
Hey.

131
00:07:52,748 --> 00:07:55,413
Is your friend a two-timer?

132
00:07:58,803 --> 00:07:59,803
No way.

133
00:08:00,211 --> 00:08:01,625
He's loyal, one love only.

134
00:08:02,533 --> 00:08:03,720
I can vouch for that.

135
00:08:03,794 --> 00:08:05,408
You can vouch for that?

136
00:08:06,396 --> 00:08:08,303
But Granny Juu never misses.

137
00:08:08,769 --> 00:08:12,122
So what does this Three of Swords
really mean?

138
00:08:20,102 --> 00:08:21,102
Sorry, sir.

139
00:08:21,253 --> 00:08:22,421
The café's closed today.

140
00:08:33,298 --> 00:08:34,311
Where's Je Meow?

141
00:08:45,737 --> 00:08:46,917
Je Meow already passed away.

142
00:08:51,824 --> 00:08:52,824
When?

143
00:09:00,619 --> 00:09:01,699
Three months ago.

144
00:09:05,601 --> 00:09:06,920
He doesn't look familiar.

145
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:09,000
This kind of guy

146
00:09:09,573 --> 00:09:11,211
coming around asking about her…

147
00:09:11,792 --> 00:09:12,908
Sorry, Lynx,

148
00:09:13,808 --> 00:09:15,415
he's gotta be her sugar baby.

149
00:09:15,562 --> 00:09:16,923
- Are you crazy?
- Yes.

150
00:09:18,290 --> 00:09:19,797
I was someone Je Meow took in.

151
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:24,910
But not in the way you're thinking.

152
00:09:31,105 --> 00:09:32,225
My name's Leo.

153
00:09:33,546 --> 00:09:34,619
I'm your brother.

154
00:09:45,289 --> 00:09:46,289
Take this.

155
00:09:51,670 --> 00:09:52,717
You might catch a cold.

156
00:10:03,954 --> 00:10:05,207
You're Kao's son, right?

157
00:10:11,591 --> 00:10:13,215
How is she?
Is she doing okay?

158
00:10:19,581 --> 00:10:20,714
She died three years ago.

159
00:10:29,033 --> 00:10:32,408
When I first met your mom,
you were still in her tummy.

160
00:10:33,034 --> 00:10:34,514
We almost got into a fight, you know.

161
00:10:35,999 --> 00:10:38,309
I thought my husband had a mistress.

162
00:10:39,170 --> 00:10:40,170
Turns out…

163
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:42,926
we'd both been played by the same guy.

164
00:10:45,753 --> 00:10:48,116
So instead, we teamed up
and beat up your dad.

165
00:10:52,587 --> 00:10:53,821
Who are you staying with now?

166
00:10:54,731 --> 00:10:56,504
With my aunt.

167
00:10:58,177 --> 00:10:59,579
She's not technically my real aunt.

168
00:10:59,655 --> 00:11:00,833
She was Mom's friend.

169
00:11:01,021 --> 00:11:02,021
I see.

170
00:11:02,647 --> 00:11:05,311
And now she won't pay for
my school anymore.

171
00:11:06,020 --> 00:11:07,214
She told me to find a job.

172
00:11:08,803 --> 00:11:11,118
Mom said if this day ever came,

173
00:11:12,452 --> 00:11:13,473
I should come find you.

174
00:11:16,064 --> 00:11:19,404
I didn't expect anything from you though.

175
00:11:19,997 --> 00:11:20,997
I just…

176
00:11:21,230 --> 00:11:22,653
came here so she can rest in peace.

177
00:11:38,428 --> 00:11:39,628
Eat this first.

178
00:12:19,094 --> 00:12:21,454
You don't have to talk formally with me.
That's just not me.

179
00:12:24,929 --> 00:12:25,929
Call me Mom.

180
00:12:28,844 --> 00:12:30,397
We're all family here.

181
00:12:32,297 --> 00:12:33,297
Hm?

182
00:12:43,071 --> 00:12:44,490
Why don't you eat the mackerel?

183
00:12:45,416 --> 00:12:47,297
Mom never told me about you.

184
00:12:47,557 --> 00:12:48,677
How would she?

185
00:12:49,820 --> 00:12:51,113
You never came home.

186
00:12:57,923 --> 00:12:59,123
Have you eaten?

187
00:12:59,291 --> 00:13:00,317
Don't worry about me.

188
00:13:00,931 --> 00:13:02,691
I can grab something
from the kitchen myself.

189
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:04,700
You don't need to.

190
00:13:05,972 --> 00:13:07,125
I'll make something for you.

191
00:13:14,606 --> 00:13:17,322
This is something I should stay out of.

192
00:13:17,954 --> 00:13:20,013
Excuse me.
I've got some ice to deliver.

193
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,414
You can go console him.

194
00:13:32,994 --> 00:13:34,110
I'm fine on my own.

195
00:14:19,628 --> 00:14:20,808
Are you okay?

196
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:24,906
How could I be okay?

197
00:14:26,583 --> 00:14:28,910
Why am I the only one
who didn't know any of this?

198
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:34,400
If Mom hadn't died,

199
00:14:35,187 --> 00:14:37,003
would I ever have known
I had a half-brother?

200
00:14:37,168 --> 00:14:40,131
Je Meow probably wanted to tell you.

201
00:14:41,316 --> 00:14:42,616
She just didn't get the chance.

202
00:14:46,546 --> 00:14:48,417
So she left me to deal
with all this alone?

203
00:14:50,730 --> 00:14:52,033
What am I supposed to do now?

204
00:14:53,319 --> 00:14:54,811
Play the perfect big brother?

205
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:00,900
Lynx,

206
00:15:02,092 --> 00:15:04,114
your mom didn't take in
every cat she met.

207
00:15:04,645 --> 00:15:05,698
I believe…

208
00:15:07,002 --> 00:15:09,117
if she chose to take care
of your brother,

209
00:15:10,871 --> 00:15:12,124
that means he wasn't a bad kid.

210
00:15:53,183 --> 00:15:54,183
Give it a try.

211
00:15:55,138 --> 00:15:57,421
I don't know if it's as good as
what Mom used to make.

212
00:16:24,926 --> 00:16:26,429
Is it as good as
when Mom made it?

213
00:16:35,678 --> 00:16:36,678
It's edible.

214
00:16:44,764 --> 00:16:47,117
How much did Mom
give you each month?

215
00:16:48,384 --> 00:16:49,404
Why do you ask?

216
00:16:51,758 --> 00:16:53,024
Are you gonna support me now?

217
00:16:55,369 --> 00:16:57,006
That's probably what Mom
wanted me to do.

218
00:17:02,265 --> 00:17:03,306
How much do you need?

219
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:07,011
If I can manage it, I'll help.

220
00:17:09,210 --> 00:17:10,210
Usually,

221
00:17:11,622 --> 00:17:13,711
the money she sent was for my rent.

222
00:17:16,752 --> 00:17:18,078
I've moved out of that place now.

223
00:17:22,243 --> 00:17:23,290
I was thinking…

224
00:17:26,124 --> 00:17:27,403
of moving in here instead.

225
00:17:54,166 --> 00:17:55,312
Do you miss me, Jumbo?

226
00:17:56,422 --> 00:17:59,308
You know I'm moving in here.

227
00:18:09,716 --> 00:18:11,026
You know Jumbo too?

228
00:18:14,021 --> 00:18:15,021
Of course.

229
00:18:15,492 --> 00:18:16,819
I named him myself.

230
00:18:17,529 --> 00:18:18,658
He was really happy about it.

231
00:18:18,682 --> 00:18:22,222
(Yeah! Thank you, Leo.)

232
00:18:25,114 --> 00:18:26,321
I already got your room ready.

233
00:18:27,782 --> 00:18:29,104
You really didn't need to.

234
00:18:29,444 --> 00:18:30,719
Whenever I stayed over,

235
00:18:31,013 --> 00:18:32,326
I always slept in Mom's room.

236
00:18:35,270 --> 00:18:36,424
I'll take Mom's room.

237
00:18:37,342 --> 00:18:38,715
You can use my room instead.

238
00:18:40,967 --> 00:18:41,967
Fine.

239
00:18:42,524 --> 00:18:45,320
I'm just someone asking for
a place to stay anyway.

240
00:19:05,892 --> 00:19:07,525
If you want to judge me, go ahead.

241
00:19:13,898 --> 00:19:14,998
I'm not gonna judge you.

242
00:19:16,783 --> 00:19:17,929
That room…

243
00:19:18,573 --> 00:19:20,221
is full of your mom's memories.

244
00:19:21,852 --> 00:19:22,911
If it were me,

245
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:24,819
I wouldn't want to give it up either.

246
00:19:27,864 --> 00:19:28,984
But from now on,

247
00:19:31,389 --> 00:19:33,749
you should start making good memories
with your brother too.

248
00:19:35,083 --> 00:19:36,117
I'm not sure about that.

249
00:19:37,231 --> 00:19:39,309
I don't know if I can.

250
00:19:40,098 --> 00:19:41,124
Of course you can.

251
00:19:41,637 --> 00:19:43,304
Look at all the cats in the café.

252
00:19:44,027 --> 00:19:45,304
You managed to tame them all.

253
00:19:49,637 --> 00:19:50,920
Ugh.

254
00:19:51,847 --> 00:19:52,994
So what?

255
00:19:53,902 --> 00:19:56,019
I haven't even tamed the latest one yet.

256
00:19:56,724 --> 00:19:58,010
And now there's another one.

257
00:19:58,727 --> 00:20:00,321
But the latest one…

258
00:20:01,715 --> 00:20:02,920
is actually easy to tame.

259
00:20:05,265 --> 00:20:06,833
Just go on a date with him. That's all.

260
00:20:08,734 --> 00:20:10,025
You've said enough.

261
00:20:10,115 --> 00:20:11,216
Go home already.

262
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:12,920
Go.

263
00:20:13,060 --> 00:20:14,060
Go where?

264
00:20:14,152 --> 00:20:15,101
Go home.

265
00:20:15,174 --> 00:20:16,174
Go on a date?

266
00:20:16,510 --> 00:20:18,523
Go home. Come on.

267
00:20:28,514 --> 00:20:29,921
Aren't you going on a date with me?

268
00:20:30,108 --> 00:20:31,108
Go home.

269
00:20:33,994 --> 00:20:35,115
I'm not talking to you now.

270
00:20:49,427 --> 00:20:50,513
Another case coming in?

271
00:20:51,613 --> 00:20:52,720
Two cats are crashing!

272
00:20:53,220 --> 00:20:54,220
Huh?

273
00:20:56,167 --> 00:20:57,213
Two cats are crashing.

274
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:58,320
What do you mean?

275
00:20:58,400 --> 00:20:59,400
Here's the thing, Doc.

276
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:01,506
We've got a new cat
moving into the café,

277
00:21:01,652 --> 00:21:03,756
but it doesn't seem to get along
with the resident cat.

278
00:21:03,780 --> 00:21:04,926
Any advice?

279
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:06,040
Oh, come on.

280
00:21:06,193 --> 00:21:07,562
I thought something serious happened.

281
00:21:07,586 --> 00:21:09,713
Cats are like lions in tiny versions.

282
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:12,999
When someone enters their territory,
they have to show who's the dominant there.

283
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:17,506
(It starts with territorial behavior,
when someone invades their space.)

284
00:21:23,586 --> 00:21:29,086
(Besides that territorial behavior,
cats are possessive and hate sharing.)

285
00:21:29,346 --> 00:21:30,346
Looking for yogurt?

286
00:21:37,420 --> 00:21:38,926
Go ahead. I'm full anyway.

287
00:21:41,053 --> 00:21:42,053
Ah.

288
00:21:44,447 --> 00:21:45,520
This tee is comfy.

289
00:21:45,707 --> 00:21:46,707
Mind if I have it?

290
00:21:47,527 --> 00:21:48,527
These too.

291
00:21:59,147 --> 00:22:00,147
(Dickhead.)

292
00:22:00,627 --> 00:22:03,706
(Lastly, cats are possessive
of their humans too.)

293
00:22:03,913 --> 00:22:06,300
(They're afraid you'll
love other cats more.)

294
00:22:06,467 --> 00:22:07,467
Hey.

295
00:22:08,360 --> 00:22:10,220
You went heavy on the perfume today.

296
00:22:16,793 --> 00:22:17,993
I almost banged my head there.

297
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:19,920
Thank you.

298
00:22:23,673 --> 00:22:24,673
It's not what you think.

299
00:22:24,807 --> 00:22:25,807
I just…

300
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:27,520
Lynx.

301
00:22:28,293 --> 00:22:29,293
Lynx!

302
00:22:30,627 --> 00:22:33,266
So what do I do

303
00:22:33,699 --> 00:22:35,000
to make Lynx and...

304
00:22:36,393 --> 00:22:39,713
I mean, to make two cats get along?

305
00:22:39,887 --> 00:22:41,326
Cats are like humans.

306
00:22:41,826 --> 00:22:43,899
You need to help them
build good memories together.

307
00:22:46,773 --> 00:22:47,906
For example,

308
00:22:48,186 --> 00:22:50,013
whenever they meet,

309
00:22:50,733 --> 00:22:52,719
let them eat something tasty together.

310
00:22:58,100 --> 00:22:59,213
Thank you so much, Doc.

311
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:01,613
I'll treat you to a meal sometime.

312
00:23:23,506 --> 00:23:24,613
What are you doing?

313
00:23:26,140 --> 00:23:27,306
I'm just trying to memorize

314
00:23:27,686 --> 00:23:29,800
how intense your scent is,

315
00:23:30,566 --> 00:23:32,366
so I don't mix you up
with someone else again.

316
00:23:32,620 --> 00:23:33,620
No need.

317
00:23:34,666 --> 00:23:36,013
I'll change it.

318
00:23:36,527 --> 00:23:38,247
I don't like using
the same thing as others.

319
00:23:38,513 --> 00:23:39,813
Are you still mad at Leo?

320
00:23:39,853 --> 00:23:40,853
Who's mad?

321
00:23:43,967 --> 00:23:45,906
I'm a good big brother.

322
00:23:46,593 --> 00:23:47,713
Why would I be mad?

323
00:23:47,819 --> 00:23:48,820
That's good then.

324
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:52,006
This Saturday's my birthday.

325
00:23:53,167 --> 00:23:54,833
How about a party,
just the three of us?

326
00:23:54,912 --> 00:23:55,912
No!

327
00:23:57,420 --> 00:23:58,933
Didn't you just say you weren't mad?

328
00:24:01,060 --> 00:24:02,060
Well…

329
00:24:02,513 --> 00:24:03,920
you want a birthday party?

330
00:24:04,407 --> 00:24:05,626
Have you been a good boy yet?

331
00:24:15,613 --> 00:24:17,093
I really have.

332
00:24:17,587 --> 00:24:18,720
If you don't believe me,

333
00:24:19,279 --> 00:24:20,999
why don't you ask
Granny Juu to pick a card?

334
00:24:24,580 --> 00:24:25,580
This card?

335
00:24:29,526 --> 00:24:30,526
The Tower.

336
00:24:32,207 --> 00:24:34,540
The Tower card means falling apart.

337
00:24:35,693 --> 00:24:38,620
I think your birthday plan
is not gonna happen.

338
00:24:41,912 --> 00:24:43,593
But I don't believe in this kind of thing.

339
00:24:44,679 --> 00:24:46,513
You pick the place for this Saturday.

340
00:24:47,607 --> 00:24:48,607
I'll pay.

341
00:24:52,780 --> 00:24:53,780
Okay.

342
00:24:54,380 --> 00:24:55,820
This good boy…

343
00:24:56,593 --> 00:24:57,926
will go scoop the litter now.

344
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,480
You two seem close.

345
00:25:10,513 --> 00:25:11,533
Are you dating?

346
00:25:15,187 --> 00:25:16,187
No.

347
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:19,460
But he seems to have feelings for you.

348
00:25:19,979 --> 00:25:20,979
I know.

349
00:25:25,453 --> 00:25:26,513
But do you know

350
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:30,733
Tiger… is totally my type?

351
00:25:32,746 --> 00:25:34,020
I think I know that too.

352
00:25:34,913 --> 00:25:36,320
Since you two aren't together yet,

353
00:25:39,027 --> 00:25:40,053
can I flirt with him?

354
00:25:43,087 --> 00:25:44,100
Go take your shot.

355
00:25:51,132 --> 00:25:52,220
If I win him over,

356
00:25:52,533 --> 00:25:53,806
I hope you'll be okay with it.

357
00:25:59,273 --> 00:26:00,606
But if you fail,

358
00:26:01,759 --> 00:26:02,980
I hope you'll be okay with it.

359
00:26:21,493 --> 00:26:23,100
Can you teach me how to make coffee?

360
00:26:23,793 --> 00:26:25,426
I wanna be useful around here,
like Lynx.

361
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:27,720
Sure.

362
00:26:34,113 --> 00:26:35,113
What?

363
00:26:35,326 --> 00:26:36,393
My dear brother Leo,

364
00:26:37,327 --> 00:26:38,813
why didn't you tell me?

365
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:43,706
I can teach you myself.

366
00:26:46,713 --> 00:26:48,906
This thing is called a portafilter.

367
00:26:49,339 --> 00:26:50,773
You put the coffee grounds in here.

368
00:26:51,872 --> 00:26:55,213
This is the milk steamer.

369
00:26:56,259 --> 00:26:57,780
You turn it like this when you use it.

370
00:26:59,073 --> 00:27:00,073
Ouch!

371
00:27:00,433 --> 00:27:01,433
Lynx.

372
00:27:01,666 --> 00:27:02,466
Are you okay?
I burnt my hand.

373
00:27:03,478 --> 00:27:04,833
I didn't know it'd be this hot.

374
00:27:09,513 --> 00:27:10,906
Ow, ow, ow.

375
00:27:15,313 --> 00:27:16,313
You okay now?

376
00:27:28,405 --> 00:27:30,712
Looks like it's gonna rain today.

377
00:27:31,390 --> 00:27:32,392
How do you know?

378
00:27:32,586 --> 00:27:33,828
The weather department said so?

379
00:27:35,017 --> 00:27:36,017
No.

380
00:27:36,390 --> 00:27:37,525
I meant you.

381
00:27:38,419 --> 00:27:40,419
You usually never come out here
and help like this.

382
00:27:42,481 --> 00:27:44,410
It's your birthday month.

383
00:27:45,924 --> 00:27:47,614
Consider it a special treatment from me.

384
00:27:48,781 --> 00:27:49,781
Really?

385
00:27:50,118 --> 00:27:51,222
I thought…

386
00:27:52,460 --> 00:27:55,292
you were trying to gatekeep me
from getting near Leo.

387
00:27:56,498 --> 00:27:57,538
Gatekeep who?

388
00:27:58,475 --> 00:27:59,926
Do I even have the right to do that?

389
00:28:00,117 --> 00:28:01,305
We're not a thing.

390
00:28:02,365 --> 00:28:03,365
Good.

391
00:28:04,466 --> 00:28:07,241
Because I don't wanna fight
with you about it later.

392
00:28:08,901 --> 00:28:09,901
Why?

393
00:28:10,407 --> 00:28:11,514
Do you like my brother?

394
00:28:16,537 --> 00:28:17,625
Why are you quiet?

395
00:28:23,064 --> 00:28:24,064
Mr. Tiger.

396
00:28:30,074 --> 00:28:31,800
If you're afraid of losing to your brother,

397
00:28:35,278 --> 00:28:36,409
how about we start dating?

398
00:28:49,513 --> 00:28:50,525
What are you saying?

399
00:28:54,469 --> 00:28:55,469
Hm?

400
00:28:56,052 --> 00:28:57,052
Lynx.

401
00:28:57,705 --> 00:28:58,763
A guy's calling you.

402
00:29:06,264 --> 00:29:07,296
It's my friend.

403
00:29:21,655 --> 00:29:22,724
Hello. What's up?

404
00:29:22,798 --> 00:29:23,598
(Hey, Lynx.)

405
00:29:23,699 --> 00:29:26,712
(I accidentally took on two jobs
at the same time.)

406
00:29:26,827 --> 00:29:28,429
(Can you cover one for me?)

407
00:29:28,879 --> 00:29:31,529
Come on, I told you
I stopped taking interpreter jobs.

408
00:29:31,850 --> 00:29:32,679
Find someone else.

409
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:34,704
(But the client
specifically asked for you.)

410
00:29:34,997 --> 00:29:36,826
(I really don't want to lose this contact.)

411
00:29:37,402 --> 00:29:39,715
(It's Friday to Sunday in Chiang Mai.)

412
00:29:39,982 --> 00:29:41,546
(The weather is really nice right now.)

413
00:29:42,711 --> 00:29:44,811
This Saturday?

414
00:29:45,567 --> 00:29:46,912
I'm not available on Saturday.

415
00:29:46,959 --> 00:29:48,523
I can take care of the café for you.

416
00:29:48,718 --> 00:29:51,371
- You can take that job.
- (Thanks so much! I'll send you the details.)

417
00:29:51,395 --> 00:29:53,408
Hey, hold on. Hey!

418
00:29:59,021 --> 00:30:00,183
Is this how you want to play?

419
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:08,016
What's going on?

420
00:30:13,390 --> 00:30:15,197
Lynx's friend called

421
00:30:15,883 --> 00:30:17,710
asking him to cover a job this Saturday.

422
00:30:17,837 --> 00:30:19,762
So I volunteered to look after
the café for him.

423
00:30:21,493 --> 00:30:22,513
But I don't know why…

424
00:30:23,596 --> 00:30:25,266
he got mad at me.

425
00:30:25,340 --> 00:30:26,860
Are you really going to try that line?

426
00:30:33,480 --> 00:30:34,480
Leo.

427
00:30:35,126 --> 00:30:36,129
Can you give us a minute?

428
00:30:36,443 --> 00:30:37,496
I'll talk to him.

429
00:30:51,828 --> 00:30:53,210
He did that on purpose.

430
00:30:53,424 --> 00:30:55,002
He knew Saturday was your birthday.

431
00:30:59,249 --> 00:31:00,296
Don't worry about it.

432
00:31:02,609 --> 00:31:04,015
Go help your friend.

433
00:31:05,835 --> 00:31:09,218
My birthday party can wait.

434
00:31:12,453 --> 00:31:16,467
Don't fight with your brother
over something so trivial.

435
00:31:38,687 --> 00:31:39,700
What are you doing?

436
00:31:40,403 --> 00:31:41,247
That's kinda cute.

437
00:31:41,341 --> 00:31:42,898
We've got this little
gimmick for customers.

438
00:31:42,922 --> 00:31:45,011
We add a cat sticker and a nice message.

439
00:31:47,218 --> 00:31:48,320
Can you write one for me?

440
00:31:48,848 --> 00:31:49,888
Make it really sweet.

441
00:31:51,514 --> 00:31:52,514
Sure.

442
00:32:57,298 --> 00:32:58,298
Tiger.

443
00:32:59,805 --> 00:33:00,805
Tiger!

444
00:33:04,303 --> 00:33:05,322
Cat overdose.

445
00:33:05,436 --> 00:33:06,886
I need to step outside for some air.

446
00:33:24,221 --> 00:33:25,835
You're actually pretty good at your job.

447
00:33:26,142 --> 00:33:27,662
Have you ever worked part-time before?

448
00:33:29,035 --> 00:33:30,217
I've done everything.

449
00:33:31,137 --> 00:33:33,725
A kid with no parents like me?

450
00:33:35,537 --> 00:33:37,457
I had to survive on my own,
any damn way I could.

451
00:33:43,191 --> 00:33:44,191
Want one?

452
00:33:49,043 --> 00:33:50,929
Nah. I quit.

453
00:33:52,823 --> 00:33:53,823
Come on.

454
00:33:54,996 --> 00:33:56,318
It's just us here.

455
00:33:59,078 --> 00:34:00,306
I won't tell Lynx.

456
00:34:16,130 --> 00:34:17,130
Hey!

457
00:34:20,150 --> 00:34:22,718
The cats here hate cigarette smells.

458
00:34:24,298 --> 00:34:25,594
If you want to stay here,

459
00:34:26,601 --> 00:34:27,708
follow the rules.

460
00:34:47,081 --> 00:34:48,303
Why are we closing early?

461
00:34:48,617 --> 00:34:49,803
It's not closing time yet.

462
00:34:52,103 --> 00:34:53,814
We've got a VIP customer

463
00:34:54,115 --> 00:34:55,414
booking a birthday party.

464
00:34:58,611 --> 00:34:59,697
We do?

465
00:35:06,207 --> 00:35:07,709
Happy birthday, Tiger.

466
00:35:22,947 --> 00:35:24,298
No cat's stopping you

467
00:35:24,739 --> 00:35:26,092
from drinking beer, right?

468
00:35:30,757 --> 00:35:31,760
I never said no.

469
00:35:45,043 --> 00:35:46,216
Just invite me too.

470
00:36:12,715 --> 00:36:13,715
Lynx.

471
00:36:14,762 --> 00:36:16,027
Why are you back early?

472
00:36:16,454 --> 00:36:18,106
I thought you'd be back tomorrow morning.

473
00:36:18,442 --> 00:36:19,918
My work finished early,

474
00:36:20,265 --> 00:36:21,723
so I wanted to come home to surprise you.

475
00:36:21,747 --> 00:36:22,747
Surprise?

476
00:36:23,551 --> 00:36:24,751
That wasn't a surprise at all.

477
00:36:26,462 --> 00:36:27,262
Lynx.
Leo.

478
00:36:28,222 --> 00:36:30,214
We've got a bunch of games for a party.

479
00:36:30,327 --> 00:36:33,367
This group of games is called Clingy
Cats, perfect to play when you're drunk.

480
00:36:38,686 --> 00:36:41,211
The first game is truth or dare.

481
00:36:41,945 --> 00:36:44,696
You have to do
whatever the card says.

482
00:36:44,990 --> 00:36:47,226
If you refuse,
you drink the whole can.

483
00:36:47,540 --> 00:36:48,660
I'll go first.

484
00:36:50,121 --> 00:36:51,121
Granny Juu,

485
00:36:51,747 --> 00:36:53,881
I dare you to pet someone's head

486
00:36:54,324 --> 00:36:55,804
like they're a kitten.

487
00:37:04,939 --> 00:37:05,956
Next up, Leo.

488
00:37:07,176 --> 00:37:09,720
I dare you to scratch someone's chin.

489
00:37:11,567 --> 00:37:13,819
Excuse me, Tiger.

490
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:19,005
I dare you to

491
00:37:19,378 --> 00:37:21,318
rub your head against someone,

492
00:37:22,408 --> 00:37:23,514
just like a kitten.

493
00:37:36,094 --> 00:37:37,523
This is getting kinda awkward.

494
00:37:37,910 --> 00:37:39,713
Let's switch games.

495
00:37:40,099 --> 00:37:41,099
Next game,

496
00:37:41,565 --> 00:37:42,685
Shedding Cats.

497
00:37:43,266 --> 00:37:44,266
Go!

498
00:37:45,262 --> 00:37:46,120
Leo, your back.

499
00:37:46,207 --> 00:37:47,372
Lynx, your tummy.

500
00:37:47,399 --> 00:37:49,599
There's more on the back.
They're still there, trust me.

501
00:37:50,002 --> 00:37:51,625
Come on, Lynx, almost there.

502
00:37:56,140 --> 00:37:57,140
It's a tie.

503
00:37:57,968 --> 00:37:58,968
Next game,

504
00:37:59,027 --> 00:38:00,027
Soju Bomb.

505
00:38:02,305 --> 00:38:04,310
First one to finish wins.

506
00:38:16,128 --> 00:38:17,128
Next game,

507
00:38:17,348 --> 00:38:18,794
Cookie Face.

508
00:38:19,095 --> 00:38:20,775
First one to get it into their mouth wins.

509
00:38:20,965 --> 00:38:21,965
Go!

510
00:38:33,335 --> 00:38:35,026
Yeahhh!

511
00:38:40,191 --> 00:38:41,320
Alright, last game.

512
00:38:41,646 --> 00:38:42,720
Cup Tower.

513
00:38:43,092 --> 00:38:45,620
Stack the cups as high as you can
without using your hands.

514
00:38:46,596 --> 00:38:47,596
Got it?

515
00:38:47,791 --> 00:38:49,504
You talk too much. Get down.

516
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:51,002
Ouch.

517
00:38:51,525 --> 00:38:52,325
Start.

518
00:38:52,453 --> 00:38:53,498
Come on, Lynx.

519
00:39:00,232 --> 00:39:01,232
Hey!

520
00:39:01,377 --> 00:39:03,177
You knocked mine over, Leo!

521
00:39:07,484 --> 00:39:08,510
Hurry up, Lynx.

522
00:39:12,716 --> 00:39:13,816
Put it properly.

523
00:39:15,362 --> 00:39:17,700
Come on, Leo. It's the last one.

524
00:39:18,531 --> 00:39:19,412
Let's do this together.
What?

525
00:39:20,428 --> 00:39:21,473
Why do I have to help you?

526
00:39:21,520 --> 00:39:22,662
I'm your friggin' brother.

527
00:39:22,729 --> 00:39:23,927
Just do whatever I tell you.

528
00:39:24,436 --> 00:39:25,436
Get over here.

529
00:39:26,063 --> 00:39:27,063
Hey!

530
00:39:35,085 --> 00:39:36,983
Yeah!!!!

531
00:39:40,188 --> 00:39:42,617
Argh.

532
00:39:45,233 --> 00:39:50,266
So this is what
Granny Juu's Tower card meant.

533
00:40:10,533 --> 00:40:11,533
Lynx.

534
00:40:12,020 --> 00:40:13,020
Lynx.

535
00:40:13,560 --> 00:40:14,560
Lynx.

536
00:40:14,853 --> 00:40:15,926
Want to go sleep upstairs?

537
00:40:17,233 --> 00:40:18,233
Lynx.

538
00:40:24,667 --> 00:40:25,667
Leo.

539
00:40:25,966 --> 00:40:26,966
Leo.

540
00:40:27,493 --> 00:40:28,592
Want to go sleep upstairs?

541
00:40:29,433 --> 00:40:30,233
Leo.

542
00:40:30,340 --> 00:40:31,340
Hm?

543
00:40:37,147 --> 00:40:38,147
Come on.

544
00:40:38,839 --> 00:40:39,839
Let's go.

545
00:40:44,873 --> 00:40:45,906
You okay, Leo?

546
00:40:55,153 --> 00:40:56,153
Careful, Leo.

547
00:40:59,339 --> 00:41:00,339
Tiger.

548
00:41:19,566 --> 00:41:21,113
Can I go into Mom's room?

549
00:42:16,160 --> 00:42:17,160
Why Mom?

550
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:22,193
I promised you…

551
00:42:23,827 --> 00:42:25,406
I'd bring you my diploma.

552
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:33,613
Why didn't you wait for me?

553
00:42:42,433 --> 00:42:43,826
Didn't you say…

554
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:47,126
we'd take photos together?

555
00:43:02,240 --> 00:43:04,526
You didn't even give me
a chance to say goodbye.

556
00:43:27,519 --> 00:43:31,646
♪ It must be you who
healed my heart again ♪

557
00:43:31,900 --> 00:43:34,473
♪ Used to ache with pain ♪

558
00:43:34,587 --> 00:43:40,813
♪ It feels so good now
with you by my side ♪

559
00:43:41,327 --> 00:43:45,880
♪ I'll hold you close, won't
let go, won't let it fade ♪

560
00:43:46,193 --> 00:43:51,053
♪ This warm and steady space you made ♪

561
00:43:51,147 --> 00:43:54,667
♪ 'Cause it's you ♪

562
00:44:15,753 --> 00:44:17,513
You're really bad at
fake sleeping, you know.

563
00:44:29,887 --> 00:44:31,406
If you're worried about your brother,

564
00:44:31,640 --> 00:44:34,620
go talk to him.

565
00:44:45,640 --> 00:44:46,706
Can you stand on your own?

566
00:44:57,420 --> 00:44:58,506
Can you take me?

567
00:45:35,027 --> 00:45:37,620
Yuck, you smell like cigarettes.

568
00:45:39,667 --> 00:45:43,793
But this smell is what tells you

569
00:45:44,325 --> 00:45:45,906
you're not alone anymore.

570
00:46:11,940 --> 00:46:12,980
Get some rest.

571
00:46:14,080 --> 00:46:15,306
You've had a long day.

572
00:46:37,693 --> 00:46:38,720
Happy birthday.

573
00:46:40,093 --> 00:46:41,093
Thank you.

574
00:46:43,560 --> 00:46:47,420
So… where's my gift?

575
00:46:50,300 --> 00:46:51,300
Do you…

576
00:46:55,193 --> 00:46:56,433
want to caress my head?

577
00:47:04,465 --> 00:47:05,600
Would that be okay with you?

578
00:47:09,184 --> 00:47:10,184
Why not?

579
00:47:13,986 --> 00:47:15,526
You could do that with Leo.

580
00:47:18,486 --> 00:47:19,706
It's not the same.

581
00:47:26,070 --> 00:47:27,110
You like Leo?

582
00:47:31,972 --> 00:47:34,533
Just tell me. I won't be mad.

583
00:47:37,186 --> 00:47:38,333
When I like someone,

584
00:47:41,746 --> 00:47:42,826
this is what I do.

585
00:48:35,526 --> 00:48:36,526
Thank you

586
00:48:37,866 --> 00:48:39,013
for this birthday gift.

587
00:48:39,038 --> 00:48:42,320
♪ I'll hold you close, won't
let go, won't let it fade ♪

588
00:48:42,527 --> 00:48:47,379
♪ This warm and steady space you made ♪

589
00:48:47,440 --> 00:48:55,093
♪ 'Cause it's you, I found my home ♪

590
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:05,008
(Next Episode) Mom once planned a trip to
search for cats around Korat with friends.

591
00:49:05,032 --> 00:49:06,206
But she never got to go…

592
00:49:06,407 --> 00:49:08,087
Since we're already here,

593
00:49:08,607 --> 00:49:10,207
how about we go find those cats for her?

594
00:49:10,540 --> 00:49:12,313
You still owe me a date, remember?

595
00:49:13,193 --> 00:49:14,326
Can I ask you something?

596
00:49:15,287 --> 00:49:16,820
Why do you want to be my boyfriend?

597
00:49:19,613 --> 00:49:22,626
When you want a cat, do you need a reason?

598
00:49:23,880 --> 00:49:26,952
If you want to embrace
me, you can't be just anyone.
